snippet: An auction for 100 wooded acres where a nine-month standoff between an antigovernment couple and federal agents took place closed without any bids on Friday.
abstract: Auction to sell off 100 wooded acres in New Hampshire where nine-month standoff between an antigovernment couple Edward and Elaine Brown and federal agents took place closes without bids, possibly because of fears land could be booby-trapped.
lead_paragraph: An auction for 100 wooded acres where a nine-month standoff between an antigovernment couple and federal agents took place closed without any bids on Friday.

headline.main: New Hampshire: No Buyers for Site of 2007 Standoff
headline.print_headline: New Hampshire: No Buyers for Site of 2007 Standoff
